A, A_1, A_2, \ldots
\chi_{A_n} \to \chi_{A}
P(A_n \triangle A) \to 0
"\implies"
\omega \in A
A \subset A_n
n \geq N
A_n \triangle A = A_n \setminus A
P(A_n \triangle A) = P(A_n)- P(A)
"\impliedby"
\chi_{A_n \triangle A} = \chi_{A_n} + \chi_{A} - 2\chi_{A_n \cap A}
\Leftarrow
\epsilon>0
\Rightarrow
\epsilon=1
\{|\chi_{A_n}-\chi_A|<\epsilon  \} \supseteq \{|\chi_{A_n}-\chi_A|<\min (\epsilon,1)  \} = \Omega \setminus \left(A_n\bigtriangleup A\right).
